1
00:13:21,547 --> 00:13:22,741
Packer.
Packer﻿

2
00:13:23,667 --> 00:13:24,861
<i>Yes, Mr Vaughn?</i>
什么事, Vaughn 先生

3
00:13:24,947 --> 00:13:27,905
Packer, those two uninvited guests
we had this morning,
Packer, 今天早上那两位不速之客

4
00:13:27,987 --> 00:13:30,220
- I assume they were photographed?
- Yes, sir.
- 我估计给他们拍照了吧？  - 是的, 先生

5
00:13:30,347 --> 00:13:32,636
Have some prints taken and sent up to me.
打印几份, 送到我这里来

6
00:13:49,247 --> 00:13:52,245
- Well, what do we do now, Doctor?
- Accept the situation, Jamie.
- 怎样, 我们现在怎么做, 博士？  - 接受现状, Jamie

7
00:13:52,347 --> 00:13:54,402
Nothing else we can do.
我们没什么可做的

8
00:14:01,507 --> 00:14:05,217
You're still worried about
your two friends, aren't you? Why?
你还是担心你的两个朋友, 是不？为什么？

9
00:14:05,307 --> 00:14:06,865
Oh, I don't know.
噢, 我不知道

10
00:14:06,947 --> 00:14:09,257
I've just got this feeling
that something's happened to them.
我只是有这种感觉, 有事发生在他们身上了

11
00:14:09,357 --> 00:14:12,984
- Why on earth should it have?
- No reason at all, really.
- 到底为什么会有事呢？  - 完全没理由, 真的

12
00:14:13,067 --> 00:14:16,097
It's not a logical conclusion, just intuition.
不是一个有逻辑的结论, 只是直觉

13
00:14:16,227 --> 00:14:18,936
Well, I'll tell you what we'll do, then.
好, 那我告诉你我们该怎么做

14
00:14:19,027 --> 00:14:21,016
- We'll go right out after them, okay?
- Oh, yes, please.
- 我们这就出去找他们, ＯＫ？  - 哦, 好

15
00:14:21,107 --> 00:14:22,763
But we'd better leave a note for them,
但我们最好给他们留个信息

16
00:14:22,856 --> 00:14:24,563
just in case they come back when we're not here.
以免他们回来时我们又不在

17
00:15:13,687 --> 00:15:15,564
Would you mind telling us what all this is about?
你能否告诉我们, 这都是怎么一回事吗？

18
00:15:15,647 --> 00:15:17,996
- You'll find out, sir.
- Sir?
- 你会明白的, 先生  - 先生?

20
00:15:23,367 --> 00:15:24,800
- All right, Benton, thank you.  - Sir.
- 没事了, Benton, 谢谢你  - 是

21
00:15:24,887 --> 00:15:27,082
- NAAFI break, sir?  - Very well.
- NAAFI 有间歇了(?)， 长官？  - 很好
<i>(NAAFI: 英国陆海空三军合作所)</i>

22
00:15:28,407 --> 00:15:30,284
How nice to see you again, Doctor.
很高兴再见到你, 博士

23
00:15:30,367 --> 00:15:32,961
It's Colonel Lethbridge-Stewart!
是 Lethbridge-Stewart 上校！

24
00:15:33,047 --> 00:15:35,720
Ah, Brigadier now. I've gone up in the world.
啊, 现在是准将了．我在这里升职了

25
00:15:35,807 --> 00:15:37,957
Of course, the Yetis. We met you in the...
当然了, 雪怪那回, 我们跟你碰过面, 在...

26
00:15:38,047 --> 00:15:39,366
That's right, McCrimmon, in the Underground.
对的, McCrimmon, 在地下

27
00:15:39,447 --> 00:15:40,880
Must be four years ago now.
肯定是四年以前了

28
00:15:40,967 --> 00:15:43,276
That long. It only seems like
a couple of weeks ago, doesn't it?
那么久？感觉好像才几个星期而已, 是吧？

29
00:15:43,367 --> 00:15:47,042
I've told you over and over again, Jamie.
Time is relative.
我跟你说了一遍又一遍, Jamie．时间是相对的

30
00:15:47,367 --> 00:15:50,757
Are you still making a nonsense of it, Doctor,
in your... What was it called?
你还在讲这些笑话吗, 博士, 在你的...它是叫什么来着？

31
00:15:50,847 --> 00:15:52,758
- Tardis?  - Yes, we're still travelling. Yes.
- TARDIS?  - 是的, 我们还在旅行, 是的

32
00:15:52,847 --> 00:15:54,838
Yes, Mr Travers told me all about it.
是, Travers 先生都说给我听了

33
00:15:54,927 --> 00:15:56,918
It's, um... Well, it's...
那是个, 嗯...怎么说, 是个...

34
00:15:57,007 --> 00:15:58,963
To say the least, an unbelievable machine.
简单说吧, 一台不可思议的机器

35
00:15:59,047 --> 00:16:02,039
DOCTOR: Any more unbelievable than the Yetis, hmm?
比雪怪还不可思议吗, 嗯？

36
00:16:02,127 --> 00:16:04,761
No, true. I'm not quite
so much of a sceptic as I was 
没有, 的确．我不再像以前那样怀疑这些

36
00:16:04,857 --> 00:16:07,361
- since that little escapade.
- But what's all this,
- 就自打上次灵异事件之后  - 但这些都是什么意思？

37
00:16:07,447 --> 00:16:09,642
and why all the cloak and dagger stuff
to bring us here?
为什么这些带着斗篷和剑的家伙把我们带到这里来?

38
00:16:09,727 --> 00:16:13,242
Yes, I'm sorry about that, but my chaps have to
be a bit melodramatic in their methods.
是的, 对此我表示抱歉．但我的人必须在执行力上强一些

39
00:16:13,327 --> 00:16:14,726
But I'll explain. Oh, do sit down.
但我会解释的．哦, 请坐下吧

40
00:16:14,807 --> 00:16:16,604
- Thank you.  - How nice.
- 谢谢你  - 很好

41
00:16:29,387 --> 00:16:31,582
(WHIRRING)

42
00:16:41,427 --> 00:16:43,736
Has the information been considered?
这个信息已经考虑过了吗？

43
00:16:43,827 --> 00:16:46,466
COMMUNICATOR: <i>The images of the two humans</i>
这两个人的图像

44
00:16:46,547 --> 00:16:50,017
<i>have been analysed and registered.</i>
已经被分析和记录了

45
00:16:50,747 --> 00:16:54,342
<i>They are known and are hostile.</i>
他们是已知的敌人

46
00:16:54,427 --> 00:16:56,941
Hostile? How can that be?
敌人？怎么可能呢？

47
00:16:57,027 --> 00:16:58,824
Have you been on Earth before?
你们以前到过地球吗？

48
00:16:58,907 --> 00:17:02,536
<i>No, they have been recognised</i>
没有, 他们已经被认出来了

49
00:17:02,607 --> 00:17:06,919
<i>They are dangerous and must be destroyed.</i>
他们很危险, 必须被消灭

50
00:17:08,127 --> 00:17:09,756
Yes, well, since the Yeti do,
是的, 自从雪怪事件以后

51
00:17:09,860 --> 00:17:11,787
I've been in charge of an independent intelligence group
我就负责了一个独立的情报组

52
00:17:11,847 --> 00:17:15,283
that we call UNIT, that's
United Nations Intelligence Taskforce.
我们叫它 UNIT, 也就是＂联合国情报行动组＂

53
00:17:15,367 --> 00:17:18,086
You mean you're like a... A world secret police?
你是说, 你就像一个...秘密的世界警察？

54
00:17:18,167 --> 00:17:21,125
Not quite. We don't actually arrest people,
we just investigate them.
不大对．我们实际上并不逮捕人, 我们只是调查他们

55
00:17:21,207 --> 00:17:22,879
What about us? I mean, you arrested us.
那我们呢？我是说, 你逮捕了我们

56
00:17:22,967 --> 00:17:24,002
Not really.
并不是

57
00:17:24,087 --> 00:17:27,284
You see, my men were keeping a watch on
the International Electromatic Headquarters
你看, 我的人一直在监视国际电气自动话公司的总部

58
00:17:27,367 --> 00:17:28,516
when you two showed up.
这时候你们俩出现了

59
00:17:28,607 --> 00:17:31,075
I've been keeping a check
on everyone going in that building.
我一直在核查进入那栋大楼的每一个人

60
00:17:31,167 --> 00:17:34,000
Your photographs were transmitted
to this Headquarters and I recognised you.
你们的照片传到总部, 我认出了你们

61
00:17:34,087 --> 00:17:36,885
Well, what's so odd about
people going into the building?
那, 进入那栋大楼的有什么奇怪的？

62
00:17:36,967 --> 00:17:38,958
Oh, nothing odd about them going in.
噢, 进入的人倒没有什么奇怪

63
00:17:39,047 --> 00:17:40,924
The problem is some of them haven't come out.
问题在于有些人一直没有出来

64
00:17:57,247 --> 00:18:01,638
BRIGADIER: This is Gordon Jones,
lecturer in physics, Churchill College, Cambridge.
这位是 Gordon Jones, 物理学讲师, 剑桥丘吉尔学院

65
00:18:01,927 --> 00:18:05,522
Next one's a chap I knew at Sandhurst,
old Billy Rutlidge.
下一个是我在 Sandhurst 就认识的, 老 Billy Rutlidge
<i>(Sandhurst 是英国陆军官校所在地)</i>

66
00:18:05,607 --> 00:18:08,565
He's got himself a very cushy number
at the Ministry of Defence.
他给自己在国防部找了一个待遇很不错的岗位

67
00:18:08,647 --> 00:18:12,560
And all these people went into the building,
the IE building, and didn't come out.
这些人都走进了那栋大楼, IE 的大楼, 然后没有出来

68
00:18:12,647 --> 00:18:14,478
No, no, most of them came out again,
不, 不, 他们中大多数人又出来了

69
00:18:14,567 --> 00:18:17,798
but there was something definitely odd
about them when they did.
但他们出来的时候绝对都有些古怪

70
00:18:17,887 --> 00:18:19,002
Odd?
古怪？

71
00:18:19,147 --> 00:18:20,944
Ah, yes, Miss Watkins.
啊, 是, Watkins 小姐

72
00:18:21,067 --> 00:18:23,103
You're concerned about your uncle, aren't you?
你在担心你的叔叔, 是吗？

73
00:18:23,187 --> 00:18:24,700
I'd like to know where he is, yes.
是, 我想知道他在那里

74
00:18:24,787 --> 00:18:28,496
He's perfectly well, I assure you,
although a little, uh...
他非常好, 我可以向你保证, 虽然有一点...

75
00:18:29,627 --> 00:18:31,777
uncooperative at the moment.
目前来说不太合作

76
00:18:32,827 --> 00:18:35,261
Your visit here is most opportune.
你们来的时机相当好

77
00:18:35,947 --> 00:18:38,461
I think that you can be very useful to me.
我觉得你会对我非常有用

78
00:18:38,547 --> 00:18:40,299
Me? But... But how?
我？但是...怎么会？

79
00:18:40,547 --> 00:18:45,257
Your uncle needs to be ''persuaded''
to continue his work for me.
你叔叔需要一点＂说服＂工作, 才能继续为我服务

80
00:18:45,627 --> 00:18:48,095
But I can't do anything about that.
但我对此做不了什么

81
00:18:48,187 --> 00:18:49,222
No.
不能

82
00:18:50,107 --> 00:18:51,745
But I can. Now...
但我可以．现在...

83
00:18:52,707 --> 00:18:56,859
Packer, I'd like you to take care
of these two young ladies, please.
Packer, 我想请你照顾一下这两位年轻的女士

84
00:18:58,227 --> 00:18:59,546
Take them!
把她们带走！

85
00:18:59,867 --> 00:19:01,380
(GIRLS PROTESTING)

86
00:19:04,567 --> 00:19:07,161
Um, Brigadier, tell me more about this
唔, 准将, 多告诉我一些信息

87
00:19:07,247 --> 00:19:09,841
International Electromatics setup.
关于这个国际电气自动化公司的情况

88
00:19:09,967 --> 00:19:11,685
Well, there isn't much to tell.
这个, 没有太多可说的

89
00:19:11,767 --> 00:19:14,706
The head of the group
is a man named Tobias Vaughn.
这个组织的头儿是一个叫做 Tobias Vaughn 的人

90
00:19:14,807 --> 00:19:16,155
Oh, yes, we've met him. A nice man. 
哦, 是的, 我已经见过他了．一个不错的人

91
00:19:16,247 --> 00:19:18,196
- He gave me this.  - Jamie.
- 他给了我们这个  - Jamie﻿

92
00:19:18,407 --> 00:19:20,602
- Oh, yes, that's just the small stuff.
- Put it away.
- 噢, 是的, 就是这种小东西  - 把它收起来

93
00:19:20,687 --> 00:19:23,565
They control practically
all of the major computer lines.
他们实际上控制了几乎所有主要的电脑生产线

94
00:19:23,647 --> 00:19:27,037
They made their real breakthrough
in micromonolithic circuit designing.
他们在微型单晶片电路设计方面还真有些突破

95
00:19:27,127 --> 00:19:28,924
Undercutting practically everyone else
on the market.
事实上把市场上的其他对手都挤出去了

96
00:19:29,007 --> 00:19:30,520
But what's your interest in this?
但你们为什么对这个感兴趣？

97
00:19:30,607 --> 00:19:33,724
Well, I knew a little about Vaughn
before his sudden success.
在 Vaughn 突然成功之前, 我对它知之甚少

98
00:19:33,807 --> 00:19:37,880
I put out a routine check on him and
we came up with one or two things of interest.
我对他进行了例行检查, 发现了一两项感兴趣的事情

99
00:19:37,967 --> 00:19:40,606
Like the disappearance of Professor Watkins.
比如 Watkins 教授的失踪

100
00:19:40,687 --> 00:19:42,518
- Yes.  - Ah, see.
- 是的  - 啊, 明白了

101
00:19:44,447 --> 00:19:48,759
I... I don't suppose you have any authority
我...我觉得你们没有得到授权

102
00:19:48,847 --> 00:19:50,519
to search the building, have you?
能够搜查这栋大楼, 有吗？

103
00:19:50,607 --> 00:19:54,600
No, Vaughn's too powerful,
he's got too many top people on his side.
不, Vaughn 很有手段．在高层里面有太多人站在他这边

104
00:19:54,687 --> 00:19:58,805
You see, Doctor, I daren't make a move against him
unless I have good reason to do so.
你看, 博士, 我不敢对他有任何动作, 除非我有很好的理由

105
00:19:58,887 --> 00:20:02,197
Well, it looks to me,
if Jamie and I want to find the Professor,
哦, 在我看来, 如果 Jamie 和我想要去找教授

106
00:20:02,287 --> 00:20:04,084
we'll have to do it in our own way.
我们就只能用自己的方法

107
00:20:04,167 --> 00:20:05,998
That's about the sum of it.
总体来说就是这样

108
00:20:06,087 --> 00:20:09,045
However, should you find yourself
in any difficulty...
但是, 如果你们遇到任何困难...

109
00:20:09,127 --> 00:20:10,765
Sergeant Walters!
Walters 中士

110
00:20:12,367 --> 00:20:14,562
- Yes, sir?  - Got a TM-45 handy?
- 是, 长官？  - 手上有 TM-45?

111
00:20:14,847 --> 00:20:16,075
Yes, sir. Right here.
有, 长官, 就在这里

112
00:20:16,167 --> 00:20:17,361
- Is that a tank?  - Oh, no, no.
- 那是一架塔克吗？  - 噢, 不, 不是

113
00:20:17,447 --> 00:20:18,641
My units are on constant alert,
我的部队会保持警惕

114
00:20:18,727 --> 00:20:20,066
so should you find yourselves in any trouble,
所以如果你们发现自己遇到任何麻烦

115
00:20:20,147 --> 00:20:23,005
- you can just give us a call.
- Jolly good!
- 就可以呼叫我们  - 太好了 

116
00:20:23,087 --> 00:20:24,805
- Here you are, sir.
- Thank you, Sergeant.
- 给你, 长官  - 谢谢你, 中士

117
00:20:24,887 --> 00:20:26,764
Now, this is a small transceiver,
看, 这是一个小型收发器

118
00:20:26,847 --> 00:20:29,356
range of about fifty miles on a set frequency.
在预定频率上有效范围大概是50英里

119
00:20:29,747 --> 00:20:30,820
Just press this button and ask for me.
只要按这个钮就可以找我就可以了  

120
00:20:30,907 --> 00:20:33,804
Oh, yes, that's splendid! Yes.
This should come in very handy.
噢, 好, 这太棒了！是的，这应该非常方便

121
00:20:33,887 --> 00:20:36,355
Call me anytime. I'm usually available.
随时呼我, 我一般都在

122
00:20:40,387 --> 00:20:42,537
No. They must have gone out.
不, 他们肯定已经走了

123
00:20:44,227 --> 00:20:45,296
Zoe?
Zoe?﻿

124
00:20:46,827 --> 00:20:48,055
Isobel?
Isobel?﻿

125
00:20:48,947 --> 00:20:50,903
Probably gone for a walk.
可能出去散步了

126
00:20:50,987 --> 00:20:53,501
Look, Jamie, sandwiches. I'm hungry.
看, Jamie, 三明治．我饿了

127
00:20:54,067 --> 00:20:55,898
- Want one?  - Thank you.
- 来一个吗？  - 谢谢你

128
00:20:57,987 --> 00:21:02,060
You know, Doctor, that chap Mr Vaughn
doesn't seem such a bad man.
知道吗, 博士, Vaughn 那个家伙看着并不像是个坏人

129
00:21:02,147 --> 00:21:03,216
(TURNS RADIO ON)

130
00:21:03,307 --> 00:21:04,706
Oh, Jamie!
噢, Jamie!

131
00:21:04,787 --> 00:21:06,698
How can I think when you've got that thing on?
你把这玩意儿打开我还怎么思考？

132
00:21:06,787 --> 00:21:07,856
Hey!
嘿！

133
00:21:09,027 --> 00:21:10,858
All right, all right.
好吧, 好吧

134
00:21:11,867 --> 00:21:13,937
- Don't break it.  - All right!
- 别弄坏了  - 没事的！

135
00:21:14,107 --> 00:21:17,065
I just want to have a look at it, that's all.
我只是想看一眼这东西, 仅此而已

136
00:21:17,587 --> 00:21:18,815
Oh, yes.
噢, 对了

137
00:21:20,347 --> 00:21:23,305
- It's an interesting little piece...
- What?
- 这是个有意思的小东西...  - 什么？

138
00:21:25,467 --> 00:21:27,059
Well, well, well.
好, 好, 好

139
00:21:29,187 --> 00:21:30,540
What have we here?
看看我们这有什么？

140
00:21:30,627 --> 00:21:32,697
What do you mean, ''What have we here?''
你什么意思, ＂看看我们这里有什么＂

141
00:21:33,067 --> 00:21:37,345
There's a micromonolithic circuit
in the back plate of this radio.
在这个收音机的后面板上有一个微型单晶片电路

142
00:21:37,507 --> 00:21:38,781
Well, what's that?
哦, 那是什么？

143
00:21:38,867 --> 00:21:40,937
It's a very complex circuit in miniature.
是一种非常复杂的电路, 做得很小

144
00:21:41,027 --> 00:21:42,938
What's so odd about that, then?
那又有什么奇怪的？

145
00:21:43,027 --> 00:21:45,222
It has nothing to do with the radio,
as far as I can see.
就我的观察, 它跟收音机功能无关

146
00:21:45,307 --> 00:21:48,777
- Oh, Doctor, just put it back together again!
- All right.
- 噢, 博士, 还是把它放回去吧！  - 好吧

147
00:21:48,867 --> 00:21:52,143
I don't suppose Zoe would have
left a note, do you?
我觉得 Zoe 不会留一张字条, 你说呢？

148
00:21:56,387 --> 00:21:59,982
No, I can't see anything.
Well, you might at least help me look for it.
我也什么都没看见．是了, 你至少可以帮我找一下

149
00:22:00,067 --> 00:22:02,103
I suggest we try the wall.
我建议我们看看墙上

150
00:22:02,187 --> 00:22:03,222
Eh?
嗯？

151
00:22:03,307 --> 00:22:05,946
Isobel never writes anything on paper.
Isobel 从不把东西写在纸上

152
00:22:06,347 --> 00:22:08,941
